That would probably be painful to track down from the end-result, and I happened to come across it while looking at #3308, so I thought it would be worth mentioning. This is probably related to 4b838af40d77684539dd40461bd92e6e453fe675

Normally, I might put together a pull request, but I don't have a CI3 environment in which to test a change at the moment. Just from looking at the code, you could go with:
- call `_error_handler()` directly (easy fix, but maintains the long-term issue that caused this in the first place), or
- throw an exception (or, worse yet, pass an Exception to `_exception_handler()`)

I would suggest something along the lines of:

```
    public function __call($method, $args = array())
    {
        if (in_array($method, $this->_methods))
        {
            return call_user_func_array(array($this->_parent, $method), $args);
        }
        throw new BadMethodCallException("No such method '{$method}'");
    }
```
